<p>This is the XR-4 &#8216;Focal Edition&#8217; which includes eye-tracked auto-focus passthrough cameras to achieve the claimed 51 PPD passthrough resolution. The &#8216;standard edition&#8217; XR has nearly identical specs, except without the auto-focus camera, the company says the headset&#8217;s passthrough resolution drops to 33 PPD.</p>
<p>As for pricing, while the Focal Edition is seriously pricey, the standard edition is actually cheaper than its predecessor; the XR-3 was priced at $5,500 for the headset alone, plus a required $1,500 annual support charge. XR-4 standard edition meanwhile is priced at $4,000 and does not require an annual support charge.</p>
<p>Varjo is also making two &#8216;Secure Edition&#8217; variants of the XR-4 (which mirror the specs of the Focal Edition and standard edition, but these are TAA compliant and can be ordered without any wireless radios (this is for particularly niche applications where data security is critical, for instance in military applications). These are priced even higher, at $8,000 and $14,000 respectively.</p>
<p><a href="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-115271" src="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-640x360.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-640x360.jpg 640w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-125x70.jpg 125w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-320x180.jpg 320w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-768x432.jpg 768w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-747x420.jpg 747w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/varjo-xr-4-announcement-4-681x383.jpg 681w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>The headset-tracked controllers are made in partnership with Razer, which has <a href="https://www.roadtovr.com/razer-quest-2-head-strap-facial-interface/">previously dabbled with various VR accessories</a>.</p>
<p>Varjo says the XR-4 will begin shipping by the end of 2023.</p>
